8 An Act relating to building codes; directing the
Department of Human Services to work with the State
9 Fire Marshal to develop certain guidelines; providing
that certain child care homes shall not be denied a
10 license; prohibiting stricter requirements; providing
for codification; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1000.31 of Title 59, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 The Department of Human Services shall work with the Oklahoma
18 State Fire Marshal to develop guidelines that allow family child
19 care homes and large child care homes, as defined in Section 402 of
20 Title 10 of the Oklahoma Statutes, to operate under the requirements
21 of the 2018 International Residential Code as adopted by the
22 Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission (OUBCC). Family child
23 care homes and large child care homes shall not be denied a license
24 to operate should they comply with the requirements of the
